1 olive oil
1 leek
1 diced bacon
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ bottle cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1.75 cup boiling water
1 packet portabello mushrooms
1 packet fusilli
1 bag parsley
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Slice portobello mushrooms and leek.

• Heat a large saucepan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook mushrooms, leek and diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-8 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and garlic & herb seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add cream (see ingredients), boiling water (1 3/4 cups for 2 people / 3 1/2 cups for 4 people), chicken-style stock powder and fusilli.
• Stir to combine and bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to medium and cover with a lid. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is 'al dente', 12-15 minutes.
• Remove from heat and stir through grated Parmesan cheese. Season with pepper.

• Divide one-pot bacon, mushroom and leek fusilli between bowls.
• Tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!